the 2015 Parish Council elections , for example , will see fundamental changes in Haslach ( SE ) .
there is then only a common parish council for all six parishes .
in a joint meeting on Saturday , the committees from Haslach , Hofstetten , Mühlenbach , Fischerbach , Steinach and Welschensteinach prepared for the changes .
the diocese &apos;s basic decisions have nothing to change and it is up to the parish council to implement them as satisfactorily as possible .
in the course of the day , it became particularly clear : skepticism about the new is hesitating but growing in confidence .
from the ideas and expectations of the innovations in 2015 to concrete proposals on the future composition and size of the parish council , the very constructive discussions between the six bodies with the main body of the soul @-@ keeping team were enough .
on the basis of a presentation , regional dekan Georg Schmitt presented the new guidelines for soul care units in the Archdiocese of Freiburg .
after that , SE Haslach , as a church community , will in future form a body of public law that will enter the rights and duties of six separate church communities .
there will only be a common parish council and a board of foundations in which the parish authority is represented .
at least two elected members are to be represented from each parish , and so @-@ called community teams are formed in the six parishes .
your task will be to promote church life in the village .
the question of the finances of the individual parish then showed considerable need for discussion .
the innovations provide for the retention of accumulated credits in the parishes .
however , the liabilities are transferred to the overall community .
particularly with regard to the large planned investments , the commitment of which was then made by all the parishes , there was great concern .
&quot; even in the past , investment was only made in projects that could be managed by the individual parishes alone , &quot; Haslach &apos;s Parish Council Chairman Bruno Prinzbach relative .
practical experience with a common body for five parish priests described Barbar Ritter , the chairman of the body in the Schutterwald @-@ Neuried Soul Unit .
in 2006 , they set themselves the task of &quot; becoming one , remaining five , &quot; and found that this is not so easy .
