in Pfullendorf , electricity is becoming more expensive
the citizens of Pfullendorfs must adapt to higher electricity costs .
as the managing director of the Stadtwerke , Jörg @-@ Arne Bias , confirmed to the SÜDKURIER , a four @-@ legged Pfullendorfer family will cost 70 to 90 euros per year .
the main reason for the forthcoming price increase is the increase in the so @-@ called EEG levy from 5.277 to 6.3 cents per kilowatt @-@ hour .
this levy is reset each year in October by the four operators of the major electricity routes .
these quantify the additional costs they incur as a result of the energy transition , which they can charge through a charge above the electricity price .
Pfullendorf is the last link in this chain .
according to Jörg @-@ Arne Bias , the Supervisory Board of the energy company even assumed a higher levy in its forecasts .
now the actual figures would have to be calculated before the city works could inform their customers of the exact price increase next week .
&quot; we expect an increase of 1 cent plus x , &quot; says Bias , with the number more close to 2 cents .
traffic light on permanent red : pay attention to waiting time
sometimes a traffic light is simply not green .
the contact cabinet in the street does not react , or the light sign is defective .
what should we do then - ride at red ?
if an affected person has waited long enough at a red traffic light and the crossing is free , he can continue , explained the lawyer Ralf Becker in the magazine &quot; Motorrad . &quot;
however , waiting time must be &quot; adequate , &quot; which can be interpreted differently from one case to another .
Becker advises you to stop at least five minutes before starting from a malfunction of the amplifier .
however , anyone who continues to drive despite red light must be aware that he is fully responsible for an accident caused by it .
anyone who tolerates less than five minutes may not wait long enough , warns Becker and points to a decision taken by the Oberlandesgericht Hamm .
in the negotiated case , a driver had ignored the traffic light after about three minutes of continuous red and had to answer for a negligent red light breach .
after all , the traffic light was not defective , but soon afterwards spread to green .
he was spared a driving ban because of the special situation - but not the fine .
