Vienna Airport issues passenger calls
Mr Max Maier , please come to Gate 24 .
in the future , there will no longer be statements like this at Vienna @-@ Schwechat Airport .
most of the speakers fail to do so - the noise level should be significantly reduced .
creating a more relaxed atmosphere is the aim of this innovation .
as Airport spokesman Peter Kleemann announced to Radio Wien , Vienna Airport follows an international trend by setting a record on individual people .
for example , airports in Copenhagen , Frankfurt or Dubai are already abandoning the noisy calls .
the removal of these divergences - on average , around 200 personal calls from the speakers on a day - is expected to make the airport quieter .
&quot; it has also been shown in experience that these individual breakthroughs have been relatively little perceived , but at the same time all other information on changed flights or departures here is a bit down , &quot; says Kleemann in conversation with the radio station .
