overview of milk and egg alternatives
vegan nutrition requires vegetable alternatives to eggs , milk and milk products .
ploughed tofu with plant gel is , for example , a quantum replacement .
other names include the Vegetarian and World Vegetarian Day on 1 November .
on the occasion of World Vegetarian Day on 1 November , Germany is proposing a number of vegan alternatives :
pure vegetable margarine is a good alternative to butter , yoghurt is replaced by soya yoghurt .
instead of milk , soya , oat , almond or rice milk can be used .
retractable planting foils replace traditional abattoirs .
there are also vegetable alternatives to eggs .
half a crushed , mature banana , for example , can replace an egg as a binder in a cake .
also 50 grams of apples or a tablespoon of laminated linseed plus three tablespoons of water are suitable for this .
loosely , dough instead of egg , for example , with a mixture of a teaspoon baking powder , a dessert starch and three tablespoons of mineral water .
but also 50 grams of soya yoghurt or soya ofu can fulfil this purpose .
according to the Vebu , around 800 000 people are currently feeding vegan in Germany , which is pure vegetable .
