UN announces new targets for poverty reduction
the United Nations is now beginning to develop a number of new objectives to replace the Millennium Development Goals on poverty reduction announced 12 years ago .
in the run @-@ up to the UN Sustainable Development Summit , which began in Rio de Janeiro in the evening , Australian diplomats played a key role in promoting &quot; Sustainable Development Goals &quot; to replace the Millennium Goals , which expire in 2015 .
they have been included in the final draft document adopted by world leaders , including Mrs Gillard , at the summit .
UN Secretary @-@ General Ban Ki @-@ moon said at the summit in the evening that the time had come to &quot; think beyond national interests . &quot;
&quot; I am pleased that member states have agreed to launch a process to agree on universal , sustainable development goals , &quot; he said .
&quot; these objectives will build on our progress in the Millennium Development Goals and will form an integral part of the post @-@ 2015 framework for development .
I will spare no effort in implementing this mandate given to me by the Member States to achieve our vision of sustainable development goals based on the success of the Millennium Goals . &quot;
