Haigerloch : Evening Church focuses on
as a contribution of the city to the 150 @-@ year @-@ old existence of the Evangelical Church in Haigerloch , the city &apos;s cultural and tourism office dedicates the last of its public theme tours on Sunday 27 October , the evening meal church .
after the visit to the Atomic Keller Museum , the Haigerlocher loch was to be considered after 1850 when Haigerloch came under Prussian rule .
the crowning end point is a visit to the Abbey Church .
there , the guides tell the story of the construction of the church and gain insights into the development of the Protestant community in a through and through Catholic territory .
last but not least , there is also a view of the evening meal created by Friedrich Schüz with the support of Walter Kröll and Georg Halbritter .
it is an original reproduction of Leonardo da Vinci &apos;s famous Milan model .
the meeting point for the other half @-@ hour tour is at the Atomic Cell Museum at 3 p.m.
