Gechingen : no absolute protection possible
&quot; we want to involve the inhabitants at an early stage in planning , &quot; Mayor Jens Houter opened the Citizens &apos; Information Event on the flood protection concept in Gechingen .
around 80 participants had come to the municipal hall to explain the planned measures , ask questions , express concerns and introduce ideas .
Houter made it clear : &quot; the final decisions take the members of the municipal council . &quot;
the floods that hit Gechingen on 15 May 2009 , unprepared , had been a major event that raised the question of safeguards for the future , says Houter .
a river basin inquiry was commissioned with the neighbouring municipality of Aidlingen , which is now the basis for the flood protection concept in Gechingen .
&quot; protecting as many land as possible is the goal , &quot; says Houter .
according to German weather services , the planning of protection against flooding is based on statistics every 100 years .
climate change is taken into account by a 15 % supplement .
this is called &quot; HQ 100aKlima . &quot;
the water masses , which caused considerable damage in Gechingen in 2009 , amounted to a 1000 year flood .
&quot; there is no absolute protection , but a relative improvement can be achieved , &quot; says Houter .
in order to protect HQ 100aClimate , around EUR 4 million will have to be invested in Gechingen , with the municipality expected to receive national subsidies of around 70 % .
Houter pointed out , however , that there would only be support if an overall approach were implemented .
this requires the participation of citizens .
an elaborate planning and authorisation procedure must be completed .
at best , implementation could start in 2016 .
among other things , the concept of protection , which was presented last week in the municipal council ( we reported ) , provides for local measures in the inflow of the river Irm from the stem of the Upper Austria Valley .
following the presentation of the flood protection concept , participants took the opportunity to raise their concerns .
among other things , it questioned why no more dams and reservoirs were planned to protect the place .
Gregor Kühn , expert planner of the commissioned engineering office Wald and Corbe from Hügelsheim , who presented the concept , stressed that it was necessary to combine all the measures presented to achieve the desired goal .
in addition , one should find the most economical solution , according to Joachim Wald von Wald and Corbe .
resentment prevailed among residents of the old town , who , even with normal storm rain , are constantly suffering from congestion on the canal network .
the problem is well known to the administration and first measures have already been taken .
however , Houter pointed out that the guidelines for Channel Systems were different from those for flood protection and that this should not be mixed .
the municipality is obliged to interpret the network in such a way that two to three years of regenerative events could be overcome .
to scale up the wastewater channels would waste millions .
