Miller said that the direct link to Bulgaria , a member of the European Union , meant that the geopolitical risks associated with transit countries were &quot; forever . &quot;
Bulgarian consumers receive gas from South Stream at favourable rates when the whole project starts operating in 2015 .
according to Gazprom , construction works in other downstream countries should begin on the planned route towards the end of the year .
the pipeline is designed for an annual capacity of 62.3 billion cubic metres of natural gas .
