Drogentunnel discovered by its own railways between the US and Mexico
one of the most refined tunnels for drug smuggling between the US and Mexico , which was fully equipped with lighting , ventilation and electrical railway operations , has now been discovered .
the US authorities described the 120 times 90 centimetres as one of the most sophisticated passages they would have ever found .
the tunnel , which runs over a length of almost six football fields , connects Lagerhallen near Tijuana , Mexico , and San Diego , USA .
in the area there are countless unseeming warehouses , making it easier to hide drug @-@ contaminated lorries .
the tunnel was closed before drugs could be transported undetected .
when the tunnel was discovered , eight and a half tonnes of marijuana and 148 kilograms of cocaine had been secured , according to the Court &apos;s records .
three men who , according to the authorities , worked as drivers were indicted for the ownership and intended sale of marijuana and cocaine .
they are threatened with prison sentences of between ten years and life .
in Nogales , Arizona , smugglers rely on an extensive underground network of dewater channels .
the tunnel is the eighth large passage discovered in San Diego since 2006 .
some of the largest tunnels were discovered after the Marihuana harvest in Central Mexico in October , putting the drug cartels at the challenge of bringing their product to consumers quickly .
in 2010 , authorities found a passage of about 640 metres with rails , which ran from a kitchen in a residential house in Tijuana to two warehouses in San Diego .
