according to Lexika , veganism is subordinate to vegetarianism , but it is very different from it .
because while vegetarians allow the consumption of cream , ice or a strong ice @-@ cream , they are not on the menu of a vegan .
milk , cheese , egg , in addition to abandoning meat and fish , leaves the vegan out of all consumption of animal products - honey is also denied .
what remains , one might wonder , but , with a closer look , the vegan food world is characterized by a remarkable ingenuity .
&quot; breads are very popular , &quot; explains Ute Henkelmann , the owner of the local Reform House , who provides a variety of special products for vegans .
Reuben Proctor also likes to visit the store in Domgasse .
for 13 years now , the native New Zealand vegan lives , in Lampertheim he finds ( almost ) everything he needs to live . &quot; in 1997 I changed my diet and became vegetarian . &quot;
at the turn of the century , the next step was taken and I became vegan .
&quot; however , the conviction came not only because of the diet , but also because of the shoe choice , &quot; says Proctor , who prefers normal leather .
he recognized that other everyday matters are not covered by animal products .
above all , vegan is an ethics .
&quot; I do not want animals to die for me , &quot; Proctor explains the maximum amount of vegans spread across all consumer behaviour .
instead of sacrificing burgers , burners or rubber bears , the vegan quickly discovered completely new products , which increased enthusiasm .
&quot; it &apos;s a double bonus , &quot; Proctor says today , &quot; in fact vegan is not a renunciation , not an amaze , but an enrichment .
and it is precisely these conditionality that left some even so well @-@ intentioned .
&quot; the addictive factor is a crucial factor that allows many to give up quickly , similar to smoking , &quot; Proctor makes a comparison .
&quot; certain tastes are not to be found on the animal . &quot;
it is often the spices or the type of preparation that make up the taste .
&quot; you can create the same effect in other ways , &quot; the vegan explains .
for example , Proctor brings aubergines , champignons and a few vegans to a barbecue party .
it pays attention to a balanced , varied diet , where it should taste defective .
of course we want something between teeth , that is legitimate .
&quot; it should taste , but that is not just to reduce animal food , &quot; Proctor said .
he did not suffer from health damage to eating disorders , another widespread assumption .
for me , the changeover had a positive aspect .
I do not take a foreign cholesterol and have an increased vitamin content .
there are high @-@ performance athletes who only feed vegan .
&quot; my blood values are excellent , I often let me check , &quot; explains Proctor .
especially the lack of vitamin B12 warn many vegansimus critics .
&quot; since animals are fed with feed instead of grazing on the pasture , it is questionable whether in the meat that is bought in the coolant the vitamin B12 is high , &quot; Proctor finds .
vegans also have the possibility to take the coenzyme in the form of tablets .
&quot; my B12 values are fine , &quot; he explains .
there was no need for Proctor to go far for food procurement .
basic foods are available everywhere and every supermarket now has soya milk and other products .
I find everything I need on the spot .
I only buy something special from time to time .
&quot; many people overlook the fact that only finished products are expensive , but that is what we know is the case with &quot; ordinary &quot; finished products . &quot;
in any case , the preparation of vegan dishes is much cheaper and less time @-@ consuming than is commonly assumed .
&quot; in the kitchen there is much to discover , with a few small knees you can achieve good , if not better , results , &quot; says Proctor .
Margarine instead of butter , a little more baking powder and carbon dioxide instead of egg , with its vegan cheese cake Proctor could also bring his butterflies to the nest .
family celebrations give the vegan a new treat .
this has a new meaning when cooking together .
&quot; the situations that may arise are as different as the people themselves , &quot; Proctor says .
of course , he has already been sceptical .
do you not taste my food anymore ?
&quot; should I feel bad now because I drink milk ? &quot; - for such questions , one has to act as a vegan with fingertips .
&quot; I am not opposed to people , I am part of this society , &quot; Proctor does not want any deadline for enclaving .
and , more precisely , everyday life does not seem as vegan @-@ like as it is believed - and the vegan is not as restricted in everyday life as commonly assumed .
fast food is also allowed .
Pommes are everywhere !
&quot; many dinosaurs offer Falafel , or even a vegetarian Yufka , &quot; Proctor says .
in a pizzeria he leaves on pasta , or orders a pizza without cheese , all a matter of habit .
the restaurants are so slow to adjust .
&quot; when I started eating vegan 13 years ago , everything was even more difficult , &quot; the New Zealand can find a development : &quot; you have to talk to people , make them aware . &quot;
&quot; if there are enough questions , they may be inclined to add to the menu , &quot; he hopes .
vegane restaurants are developing , such as the Kombüse in Mannheim or the Café Vogelfreie .
Proctor hopes that other restaurants will have at least a vegan dish on the menu .
basically vegan dishes are available for everyone .
everyone can eat them , so they are exactly the opposite of exclusive .
&quot; meat dishes are exclusive , in the truest sense of the word , because they exclude others , &quot; Proctor states .
&quot; if we want to avoid food scandals , veganism is a safe way to make the vast majority impossible from the outset , &quot; Proctor says .
the purchase of vegan products could be rather difficult at the beginning .
especially when one learns to understand that animal additives can be included in peanuts as a color donor , adherence to ethics at so many hurdles and traps seems to quickly leave the courage .
not only for this reason , Reuben Proctor and Lars Thomsen have written a book : &quot; veganissimo - animal ingredients and their alternatives &quot; explains the many ingredients that are added to food and cleaning agents .
&quot; gradually you develop a scanner view and know which characters and logos you have to pay attention to , &quot; Proctor says .
veganism , it is an important moral finger pointing to awareness .
perhaps he does not quite manage to interpret his habits , but at least he can teach consumers to question their habits critically .
