Pope Francis appoints first cardinals in February
Pope Francis was appointed for the first time on 22 February by the Catholic Church , as announced by the Vatican on Thursday .
cardinals are the most senior clerics in the Catholic Church after the Pope and they are also the ones who elect a Pope , so that Franziskus will appoint the first group of men who will eventually participate in the election of his successor .
there are currently 201 cardinals .
however , a cardinal who has reached an age of 80 can no longer take part in the ballot - that is the case of a group of 120 &quot; voting cardinal . &quot;
in a statement announcing the news , Father Federico Lombardi , a Vatican spokesman , said that there would be a meeting of all Cardinals before the ceremony was held to appoint the new Cardinals , also known as the Consistorium .
&quot; Pope Francis has decided to announce in advance his decision to convene the consistency in February so that other meetings requiring the participation of cardinal channels from all over the world can be planned , &quot; Lombardi said .
Jack Valero of Catholic Voices said that the number of voting cardinals would probably have fallen by February .
he explained that a Pope usually nominates as many cardinals as necessary so that the number of cardinals eligible to vote again amounted to 120 , and as many cardinals over 80 as he wants .
next year &apos;s consistency is important because it was the first since the election of Francis in March this year , Valero said .
at present , there is a certain overhang on the part of Europe and , in particular , Italy .
he said .
forty per cent of Catholics live in South America , but they have only a tiny number of cardinal channels .
the Cardinals will also be the first to be convened since the formation of the Franciscan Council , a group of eight Cardinals from all over the world who have the task of finding ways to reform the church .
in the past , the Pope decided everything alone .
said Valero .
he said that it was &quot; well possible &quot; that Franziskus would ask the Cardinals for advice .
but so far we have not been in this situation - that is all new .
Valero said that the bishops from large places would typically be called cardinal channels , but Franziscus &quot; is full of surprises - so we do not know who he appoints . &quot;
