Supreme Court confirms Obama &apos;s Health Law
it is a great victory for the Obama administration : the US Supreme Court today ruled that the health law closely linked to Barack Obama is constitutional .
with five to four votes , the judges ruled that the individual mandate of the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act - forcing US citizens to take out health insurance or pay a penalty by 2014 - is constitutional within the framework of the state &apos;s fiscal authority .
the chief judge John Roberts took the side of the four more liberal members of the Chamber , while the judges Scalia , Thomas , Alito and Kennedy decided against it .
the Court also upheld the remaining sections of the 2700 pages of the law and considered that the provision of the Health Act , according to which states would either have to extend the conditions of access for Medicaid or that all state aid subsidies would be removed , was not unconstitutional .
the case against the law was brought by 26 states and the National Federation of Independent Business .
the law was strongly rejected by all leading Republican presidential candidates , including the ultimate challenger Mitt Romney , in the pre @-@ election campaign in 2012 .
Norway : Norwegian place with giant mirrors
with huge mirrors , the inhabitants of a Norwegian village have brought light to their darkest valley .
due to the low sunrise , the Rjukan , located in the Vestfjord valley , normally falls in the shade of the surrounding mountains from autumn to spring .
with three gigantic reflectors at a height of 45 metres , a century dream was realized on Wednesday .
&quot; finally ! , &quot; warmed Mayor Steinar Bergsland at the launch ceremony in TV2 .
some of the people living in the valley were right to sunbeds , while others used sunglasses to be safe .
so far , sun @-@ worshippers had to go to a nearby summit with a cable car in winter .
ten years ago , the local artist Martin Andersen presented the proposal to direct the rays into the valley with mirrors .
however , this basic idea has been in place since 1913 .
after several years of debate , the City Council finally adopted the 5 million crowns ( approximately € 615 000 ) expensive project .
a similar construction has been provided to the Italian Alpine resort of Viganella for several years .
