you thought that travel agencies belong to the past thanks to the Internet ?
Flight Centre seems to resist the trend .
the company has increased its profit prospects for the whole year and expects record revenue from holiday makers in Australia and the UK .
the travel company now assumes an adjusted annual profit before taxes of between $ 325 and $ 340 million , compared to $ 305 to $ 315 million in its previous forecast .
if the current target values are met , this means growth of 12 @-@ 17 % compared to the record gain of $ 290.4 million over the period 2011 @-@ 12 .
as Managing Director Graham Turner announced , Flight Centre achieved eight percent profit in the first half of the year and recorded a strong start to the second half of the year , especially in Australia and Britain .
&quot; since the beginning of the year , our ten countries have been profitable , and some of them are on track to record annual income before interest and taxes , &quot; he said .
these include Australia and the United Kingdom , which are typically among our strongest performers .
in Australia , the leisure sector has recovered in the second half of the year , making it a slightly weaker market for business trips .
it was similarly good for Flight Centre &apos;s leisure activities in the UK , while business customers were spending less .
the US business recovered from the more seasonally weaker first half of the year , so a profit is expected for the third consecutive year .
Flight Centre shares rose by 3 cents yesterday to 38.20 dollars .
schools are encouraged to focus more on mathematics , spelling and grammar
in future , students will have to treat at least one piece of Shakespeare , a 19th century novel , romantic lyrics , and contemporary British novels from 1914 .
the test also includes &quot; unread texts &quot; to encourage wider reading .
the combined course of English literature and language will be abolished .
from 2015 onwards , students will have to pass an independent GCSE test for language , with strong incentives to choose English literature as a separate qualification .
tomorrow , the Ministry of Education will publish the new curricula for English and mathematics - the first subjects that have been radically redesigned .
other core issues will be changed next year .
in a separate initiative , Ofqual , the supervisory authority for audits , will announce a reorganisation of the GCSE structures , including a new naming system and less course work .
in a speech this summer , Education Minister Michael Gove said that there is a &quot; broad consensus that we need to reform our audit system in order to restore public confidence , &quot; stressing that the GCSes would become &quot; challenging , ambitious , and stricter . &quot;
studies show that less time is spent on mathematics in English schools - 116 hours a year or three hours a week per school year - than in most other countries .
by contrast , Australian schools teach an average of 143 hours a year and students in Singapore receive 138 hours .
while there will be no formal requirement to provide more time for mathematics in the timetable , coalitions are said to encourage schools to devote more hours to comprehensive Matheprüche , combined with a greater weighting of specialist in rankings .
the curriculum focuses more on &quot; real life problems , &quot; including financial mathematics .
