SALEM : Johanna Rahner at the Ecumenical Meeting Forum
the next Ecumenical Meeting Forum on Monday 21 October , at the New Museum of the Castle , the topic &quot; On hell with hell - Theological reflections on how to deal with the last things today . &quot;
lecturer is Professor Johanna Rahner .
the Ecumenical Meeting Forum is an initiative of the Catholic and evangelical church communities of Salem , the Castle of Salem and the Cultural Office of the Bodensee Circle .
Johanna Rahner wants to explore in the forum how people today classify the &quot; last things &quot; after death .
if people had known too much about it over the past centuries , relying on the images of heaven and hell &quot; that still characterise our ideas , &quot; the contemporary prophetic doctrine of hope for completion is characterized more by a degree of embarrassment or even a lack of language .
&quot; the greater hope has been driven out Christianity by religious critique , &quot; says the speaker .
she has &quot; supplied us with so many question marks that we seem to have lost the exclamations . &quot;
Johanna Rahner continues : &quot; but the crucial challenge remains the anger of death . &quot;
this implies the question of the yearning , &quot; who dreams that everything will be good in the end . &quot;
Johanna Rahner , born in 1962 in Baden @-@ Baden , studied Catholic theology and biology at the Albert @-@ Ludwigs @-@ Universität Freiburg .
she graduated in 1997 from Dr. theol . , also in Freiburg .
the Habilitation for Fundamentaltheology and Ecumenical Theology followed in 2003 at Wilhelms University .
since 2010 , Johanna Rahner has a chair for systematical theology at the Institute of Catholic Theology at the University of Kassel .
